<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1592,2015]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,450,1628,1655]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Original description:</emphasis>
“la forma di Capri, non rara a profondità, è corta, rigonfia e differisce da quella non solo tipica, ma di altre località mediterranee” [the 
<taxonomicName box="[671,811,1664,1690]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" rank="variety" variety="from">variety from</taxonomicName>
Capri—of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Calcara, 1845)" authorityName="Calcara" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Calcara" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[942,1431,1664,1691]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Coralliophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meyendorffii">
<emphasis box="[942,1245,1664,1690]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Coralliophila meyendorffii</emphasis>
(Calcara, 1845)
</taxonomicName>
, reported as 
<taxonomicName authority="Calcara" authorityName="Calcara" box="[281,666,1700,1726]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Pseudomurex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meyendorffi">
<emphasis box="[281,574,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Pseudomurex meyendorffi</emphasis>
Calcara
</taxonomicName>
—, not rare at depths, is short and swollen, and differs from both the typical shells and the ones from other Mediterranean localities].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="353" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1592,2015]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1773,1799]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Remarks:</emphasis>
having been instituted as a geographic race, we rank it subspecific, and thus available (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1298,1432,1773,1799]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 10, glossary). Listed as a simple variety or a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Calcara, 1845)" authorityName="Calcara" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Calcara" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[859,1345,1808,1835]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Coralliophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meyendorffii">
<emphasis box="[859,1162,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Coralliophila meyendorffii</emphasis>
(Calcara, 1845)
</taxonomicName>
by several authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Sabelli, B. &amp; Giannuzzi-Savelli, R. &amp; Bedulli, D." box="[300,512,1844,1871]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" refId="ref18986" refString="Sabelli, B., Giannuzzi-Savelli, R. &amp; Bedulli, D. (1992) Catalogo Annotato dei Molluschi Marini del Mediterraneo. Vol. 2. Libreria Naturalistica Bolognese, Bologna, 498 pp." type="book" year="1992">
Sabelli 
<emphasis box="[388,445,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">et al.</emphasis>
1992
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fasulo, G." box="[525,668,1844,1871]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" pagination="29 - 32" refId="ref16988" refString="Fasulo, G. (2012) Taxa di molluschi marini &quot; napoletani &quot; per toponimia. Notiziario S. I. M., 30 (2), 29 - 32." type="journal article" year="2012">Fasulo 2012</bibRefCitation>
), despite no figures ever being published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[1179,1354,1844,1871]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" pagination="1 - 87" refId="ref15827" refString="Bellini, R. (1929 a) I molluschi del Golfo di Napoli (studi precedenti, l'ambiente, enumerazione e sinonimia). Annuario del Museo Zoologico della R. Universita di Napoli, 6 (2), 1 - 87." type="journal article" year="1929">Bellini (1929a)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Spano, C. &amp; Murgia, D. &amp; Puddu, B." pageId="10" pageNumber="353" pagination="67 - 107" refId="ref19347" refString="Spano, C., Murgia, D. &amp; Puddu, B. (2002) Malacofaune spiaggiate della costa occidentale della Sardegna. Fisiografia e batimetria dei fondali marini di provenienza. Rendiconti del Seminario della Facolta di Scienze dell'Universita di Cagliari, 72 (2), 67 - 107." type="journal article" year="2002">
Spano 
<emphasis box="[151,209,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
listed it as a valid species, “ 
<emphasis box="[621,640,1881,1907]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">C</emphasis>
[
<emphasis box="[649,783,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">oralliophila</emphasis>
] 
<taxonomicName box="[801,907,1881,1906]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="caprensis">
<emphasis box="[801,907,1881,1906]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">caprensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, but with no further comment or description. The original description may easily fit other Mediterranean taxa than 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Calcara" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[931,1105,1916,1943]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Coralliophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meyendorffii">
<emphasis box="[931,1105,1916,1943]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">C. meyendorffii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the closer ones being 
<taxonomicName authority="(Blainville, 1832)" authorityName="Blainville" authorityYear="1832" baseAuthorityName="Blainville" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Coralliophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Coralliophila brevis</emphasis>
(Blainville, 1832)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Monterosato, 1869)" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1869" baseAuthorityName="Monterosato" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[582,1128,1952,1979]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Coralliophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="panormitana">
<emphasis box="[582,888,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Coralliophila panormitana</emphasis>
(Monterosato, 1869)
</taxonomicName>
due to original description and declared depth. Thus, it is considered a 
<emphasis box="[642,808,1988,2014]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">nomen dubium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[822,956,1989,2015]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: glossary).
</paragraph>
